  "body": "I found a minor bug when it's not able to connect to ganache-cli:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/iamdefinitelyahuman/brownie/blob/8ec17fe59e2d1b67b5d5a1c51fee46bc111daab0/brownie/network/rpc.py#L103\r\n\r\nThis line raises an RPCConnectionError, and it passes self._rpc, which cannot be None (or it crashes later in the __init__of the exceptions, trying to call poll() on it).\r\nHowever, self._rpc was set to None at the line before, in the kill() method.\r\n\r\nSo there is an inconsistency here, either kill() should not set it to None, or the exception should allow None and handle it properly.",
